\begin_layout Standard

\series medium
This section contains a description of running the Pcp-Combine tool.
 The Pcp-Combine tool is used (if needed) to modify the precipitation accumulati
on intervals from two or more gridded files into a single NetCDF file containing
 the desired accumulation interval.
 This tool enables users to define identical forecast and observation or
 analysis precipitation accumulation intervals prior to running the MET
 statistics tools.
 The "sum" command can only be run on GRIB1 or GRIB2 files while the "add"
 and "subtract" commands can be run on any gridded file.
 Use of Pcp-Combine on a single file will result in that file being written
 out in NetCDF format, with no changes to the data values.
 The files being combined must all be on a common grid.
 The Pcp-Combine tool does not support automated regridding.
 When running the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

subtract
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

sum
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 command, the input files must have the same initialization time unless
 the user has indicated that it shoud ignore the initialization time for
 the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

sum
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 command.
